description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful individual will need a &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Foundation Degree in Health and Social Care and Literacy and Numeracy Level 2 or equivalents &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;to be recruited in to this Band 4 position.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity for a permanent band 4 associate practitioner to join the dynamic SLT service within Tees, Esk and Wear Valleys NHS Foundation Trust. The successful candidate will work with the Specialist Health Team within the Durham &amp; Darlington adult learning disability service. The Specialist Health Team works alongside the Community Learning Disability Teams to support adults who need extra help with challenging behaviour or mental ill health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The SLT service works with service users with a range with communication and chewing &amp; swallowing difficulties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will include: making therapy resources and materials, gathering information and carrying out screening assessments, administering therapy programmes under the guidance of qualified therapists, assisting with delivering carer training packages, maintaining their own clinical records and carrying out a administrative duties (e.g. taking telephone messages, allocating referrals, updating spreadsheets, preparing case note files, photocopying and filing).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be access to one-to-one clinical supervision from a qualified therapist and the opportunity to attend group supervisions and SLT team meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have experience of working with people with learning disabilities, working as part of a multidisciplinary team and therapy assistant/associate practitioner experience. You will also have excellent organisational, verbal, literacy, computing and observational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must be able to work across more than one team base and travel independently to see service users in the community. There is also likely to be some home working due to the ongoing Covid-19 situation. This may involve carrying out telephone reviews and video appointments. You will have access to a laptop and work mobile phone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hannah Smibert, Specialist Speech &amp; Language Therapist on 07787983621&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;hannah.smibert@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
